<title type="html"><![CDATA[arrangement of pattern tables and name tables for background]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4770&amp;p=42262#p42262"><![CDATA[
Using consecutive tile numbers may help if you want to use increment instructions instead of lookup tables.<br /><br />Also, having a text font in ASCII order makes conversion to and from ascii easier.  Doesn't have to match the character numbers, just need to add or subtract to get ascii.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Fri Jan 23, 2009 10:26 am</p><hr />
